{{COI|date=September 2016}} {{Likeresume|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox person |name = Faisal Butt |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = |birth_place = |residence = [[London]], [[England]] |nationality = [[British Pakistanis|Pakistani-British]] |other_names = |known_for = [[Business]]'' |occupation = Entrepreneur |networth = |spouse = |children = |parents = |relations = |signature = |website = {{URL|http://www.faisalbutt.com}} }}
'''Faisal Butt''' is an entrepreneur and investor currently based in [[London]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Crofton|first=Matt|title=Looking for the next Rightmove: PrimeResi meets Faisal Butt, property’s venture capitalist with the Caan-do attitude|url=http://www.primeresi.com/looking-for-the-next-rightmove-primeresi-meets-faisal-butt/14342/|work=Prime Resi Prime Property Journal|publisher=Prime Resi|access-date=9 July 2013}}</ref>
He founded Spire Ventures in partnership with businessman [[James Caan (entrepreneur)|James Caan]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Hadley|first=Jessica|title=From MBA To Investing With A Dragon|url=http://www.businessbecause.com/news/mba-entrepreneurs/1668/from-mba-to-investing-with-a-dragon|work=Business Because|publisher=Business Because|access-date=10 July 2013}}</ref> and founded proptech investment vehicle and accelerator Pi Labs.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hadley|first=Jessica|title=Faisal Butt bio|url=http://faisalbutt.com/|work=FaisalButt.com|publisher=Squarespace|access-date=4 October 2017}}</ref>
His investment focus has a recurring theme in property, property services, and property related technology.
== Early life and education == After graduating from [[UCLA]] in 1999, Butt started his career in [[Los Angeles]] with [[American Management Systems]] (AMS), a [[Forbes]] 500 ranked IT consulting firm.{{Citation needed|date=September 2016}} In 2003 he invested and actively ran a tech start-up called Tribal Monsoon.{{Citation needed|date=September 2016}} The company was a socially conscious e-business which specialised in the sale of South Asian cultural handmade products to global businesses and consumers.<ref name="sbs">{{cite web |title=Faisal Butt |url=http://www.sbs.ox.ac.uk/centres/skoll/scholars/Pages/faisalbutt.aspx |work=University of Oxford |publisher=University of Oxford |accessdate=10 July 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130623095132/http://www.sbs.ox.ac.uk/centres/skoll/scholars/Pages/faisalbutt.aspx |archivedate=23 June 2013 |df= }}</ref>
He earned an MBA with distinction from [[Saïd Business School]], [[University of Oxford]] in 2009 as a [[Skoll Foundation]] Scholar.<ref>[http://www.sbs.ox.ac.uk/ideas-impact/skoll/scholarship/scholars/skoll-scholars-2008-9/faisal-butt Faisal Butt], Saïd Business School</ref> During his studies at Oxford, he met his eventual business partner James Caan.{{Citation needed|date=September 2016}}
Butt won “Young Entrepreneur of the Year” by [[Shell LiveWIRE|Shell]] Livewire in 2003<ref name="sbs"/> and in 2008 Oxford University's Skoll Scholarship, a highly sought-after scholarship awarded annually to five promising “social entrepreneurs”.<ref name="sbs" /> He has since featured in Top 100 Asians in UK Tech,<ref>{{cite web |title=AsiansInTech The Top 100 Asian Stars in UK Tech |url=https://asiansintech.com/top-100-asian-stars-uk-tech-2015/|work= Asians In Tech |publisher=Asians In Tech|access-date=17 October 2017}}</ref> Estates Gazette Power List 2015 and the 40 under 40 award by Property Week.<ref>{{cite web|title=Forty Under 40: Faisal Butt|url=http://www.propertyweek.com/people/40-under-40/forty-under-40-faisal-butt/5077013.article|work= Property Week 40 under 40 |publisher=Property Week|access-date=17 October 2017}}</ref> He also co-founded a South Asian chapter of the organisation [[TiE]], the world’s largest enterprise-focused non-profit.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sorrell |first=Helen |title=TiE UK Charter Member Faisal Butt is interviewed by PrimeResi |url=https://uk.tie.org/article/55/tie-uk-charter-member-faisal-butt-interviewed-primeresi |work=TIE |publisher=TIE UK |accessdate=10 July 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303220113/https://uk.tie.org/article/55/tie-uk-charter-member-faisal-butt-interviewed-primeresi |archivedate=3 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> Butt is also invested in five property ventures in five different sectors. He owns stakes in a range of companies including The Accouter Group, Ivy Gate, Opera, and 90 North.{{Citation needed|date=January 2018}}
Through his PropTech fund, PiLabs, he has also invested in tech companies such as AirSorted, AskPorter, Brolly, Built-ID, [[eMoov]], Falcon DHQ, Hubble, Land Insight, Propoly, Plentific, Rialto, Realyse, Switchee, Trussle and YourWelcome.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mathers|first=John|title=Pi Labs Investment portfolio|url=http://pilabs.co.uk/portfolio/|work=Pi Labs|publisher=Pi Labs|access-date=17 October 2017}}</ref>
