The '''Federation of Master Builders (FMB)''' is a UK [[trade association]] established in 1941<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/00368163|title=FEDERATION OF MASTER BUILDERS LIMITED - Overview (free company information from Companies House)|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> to protect the interests of small and medium-sized building firms.

The group is independent and [[non-profit]]-making, and works to lobby for members' interests at both national and local levels. As of 2016, the FMB is the largest construction trade association in the UK, representing over 8,000 construction SMEs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politicshome.com/organisation/federation-master-builders|title=Federation of Master Builders|first=|last=PoliticsHome.com|date=22 January 2015|website=politicshome.com|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref>

The FMB aims to provide knowledge, professional advice and support for its members. It works in partnership with other industry bodies to provide technical advice and promote high standards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.labc.co.uk/sponsors/fmb|title=Federation of Master Builders - LABC|website=www.labc.co.uk|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> The FMB also offers advice to consumers<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/consumer/getting-home-improvements-done/building-organisations/professional-organisations-in-the-building-industry/|title=Professional organisations in the building industry|website=citizensadvice.org.uk|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> and enables all of its members to offer warranties on their work through its insurance arm, FMB Insurance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fmbinsurance.co.uk/|title=FMB Insurance - Federation of Master Builders - Home|website=www.fmbinsurance.co.uk|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref>

