{{Infobox organization |name = Jindal Centre for Social Innovation + Entrepreneurship (JSiE) |image = Logojsie.png |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = [[Sonipat]], [[Haryana]], [[India]] |region_served = |membership = |language = |founded_date = 2014 |leader_title = Founding Director |leader_name = Jeremy Wade |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = [[O. P. Jindal Global University]] |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{URL|http://jsie.in/}} |newsletter = }} The '''Jindal Centre for Social Innovation + Entrepreneurship (JSiE)''', is a department of [[O. P. Jindal Global University]] which aims to strengthen the capacity for [[social innovation]] and provide incubation to social impact startups in the [[Delhi]], [[India]] area.
== Tibetan Entrepreneur Incubation == JSiE is an incubation partner to the Tibetan Entrepreneurship Development initiative, conducting three annual incubation cycles supporting Tibetan entrepreneurs living in India.<ref>{{cite news |title=TED Successfully Organises 3rd Business Plan Competition for 3rd Batch Entrepreneurs |author= |website=[[Tibet.net]] |date=29 June 2017 |url=http://tibet.net/2017/06/ted-successfully-organises-3rd-business-plan-competition-for-3rd-batch-entrepreneurs/ |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913184027/http://tibet.net/2017/06/ted-successfully-organises-3rd-business-plan-competition-for-3rd-batch-entrepreneurs/ |archivedate=13 September 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tibetan PM awards young entrepreneurs |author= |newspaper=[[Phayul.com]] |date=25 June 2015 |url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=36179 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304125352/http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=36179 |archivedate= 4 March 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/wire-news/tibetan-entrepreneurs-launch-new-startups-to-preserve-cultureindia_7059301.html|title=Tibetan Entrepreneurs Launch New Startups to Preserve Culture in India|website=www.moneycontrol.com|access-date=2016-07-29}}</ref> JSiE is a member of UBI Global Incubation Network and the Global Social Entrepreneurship Network.
== International Social Innovation Challenge (ISIC-15) == ISIC-15, an inaugural event organized jointly by [[O. P. Jindal Global University]], the [[University of Southampton]] and the [[Lahore University of Management Sciences]], took place in August 2015 and was designed around the theme of ‘Empowering Women through Safer Communities' in Delhi, India.<ref>{{cite news |title=Solutions For Local Problems |author= |newspaper=[[Deccan Herald]] |date=29 September 2015 |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/503368/solutions-local-problems.html}}</ref> The format consisted of students from India, Pakistan, and UK students divided into teams and undergoing 10 days of skill-focused workshops to facilitate the creation of sustainable social enterprises.<ref>{{cite news |title=Students to design venture on women safety |author= |newspaper=[[Business Line]] |date=2 September 2015 |url=http://www.bloncampus.com/b-school-corner/students-to-design-venture-on-women-safety/article7608088.ece}}</ref> ISIC-15 was featured on the [[NDTV]] program Heads-Up.<ref>{{cite episode |title=Students Without Borders |series=Heads-Up |date=18 September 2015 |url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/heads-up/students-without-borders/383427 |network=[[NDTV]] |last=Jog |first=Natasha (host)}}</ref>
