{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}}
'''Sir Robert James Kerridge''' (30 October 1901 &ndash; 26 April 1979) was a New Zealand businessman, cinema proprietor, film distributor, tourism promoter and entrepreneur. He was born in [[Christchurch]], [[North Canterbury]], [[New Zealand]] on 30 October 1901. He developed a theatre chain that owned or controlled 133 cinemas, the biggest exhibition chain in New Zealand or Australia. In 1946 Kerridge sold 50 per cent of his cinema chain to the [[J. Arthur Rank Organisation]] of London, netting the vendors almost £1 million, and a [[Rolls Royce]] car for Kerridge. The chain was renamed '''Kerridge Odeon'''.<ref name="DNZB Kerridge">{{DNZB|title=Robert James Kerridge|first= L. R.|last= Shelton|id=4k10|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

